deck: Onoli is a male were-lion, and current leader of Northern Edge Guard in the Gold Digger universe.
description:
Origin

Onoli is a naturally born were-lion raised in Jade realm, with all the normal strengths and weaknesses of were-folk. He is very level headed and is a gentle but firm leader.

Creation

Fred Perry created Onoli and the other members of the Northern Edge Guard as both representatives of other were-cat clans and as a homage to the cartoon Thundercats (of which Onoli is an anagram for Lion-o).

Character Evolution

Onoli has primarily evolved in 2 ways: his leadership skills, and his attunement to his equipment.

He took over leadership of the Northern Edge Guard when the previous leader Gaja died. Since then he has continued to improve his general leadership skills and his ability to manage the personalities of his teammates.

He continues to improve his attunement with his elemental weapons, the katanas Seraphim and Necro. This has allowed him to unlock additional powers both when combining them together and when combining them with the elemental weapons of his teammates.

Major Story Arcs

To be added later.

Powers and Abilities

Lycanthropy

In the Gold Digger universe, all were-folk are the result of permanent magical enchantments on a human's aura which are passed on either through children or the intentional transmission of bodily fluids (usually a bite). Anyone "infected" rather than born with lycanthropy is made a "thrall" of the one who infected them for some amount of time. Were-folk possess the standard abilities of enhanced physical attributes, the ability to freely shapeshift between human/hybrid/animal forms, rapid healing against non-magical damage, and weakness against damage from magic, silver, or other were-folk's fangs/claws. Due to heavy drain on their aura from their enchantments, most were-folk find it very difficult to become spell-casters.

Enhanced Strength

All were-lions possess strength enhanced beyond the norm for were-cats, making them almost as strong as a were-wolf. Onoli's training has increased this even further by a significant degree.

Skills

Onoli is competent leader with an awareness of the strengths and weaknesses of each member of his team including his own. He is also a good tactician, able to grasp a situation and make decisions, though he can not match Thropan's raw intellect. Finally he is an expert warrior both with his hands and wielding his elemental weapons, though both Gar and Tirga are better fighters.

Equipment and Weapons

Elemental Weapons

Onoli's elemental weapons are a pair of katana-like swords, called Seraphim and Necro. Seraphim possesses holy, healing powers, while Necro is the opposite. With practice, improved attunement, and meditation, Onoli continues to unlock additional abilities when using these weapons together and/or in combination with his fellow teammates' weapons.

Edge Guard Jasper of Leadership

Onoli is current owner of the Edge Guard Jasper of Leadership, a large green gem. This gem is in fact the the external form of Rain, one of three "hard ships" created by Ancient Gina and used by the trio of ancient races from the previous universe to escape its collapse. Rain is the hard ship which transported the race called the Gardeners. With attunement and meditation, Onoli has been able to perceive the inside of the hard ship as an idyllic garden tended by Gaja's spirit with whom he can talk and seek advice.
name: Onoli

deck: An amnesiac who does not know her past, who wields a magical floating orb in combat.
description:
Origin

Viola is a mysterious enigma, her memories vague and something she would struggle to hold on to. She believes she may have been born in a forest, but that one day her encampment was attacked, leaving her in its ruins with only a crystal ball she would cling to. She possesses the ability to intuitively understand and predict the future of people she meets. Viola would use this ability to make a living as a fortune teller, surviving and making enough money for food and shelter, however the eery accuracy of her precognitive powers would mean she could never stay in one location for too long. The fact that many people do not actually like to know some truths. Viola would often be attacked while she was traveling, by thieves and bandits, however Viola was not an easy victim, she was a trained fighter, welding a metal claw and with the ability to use her crystal ball as a weapon. As odd was Viola's inability to hold onto her own memories for very long.

Constantly traveling and coldness earned from strangers who were displeased with her predictions, fostered a sense of apathy and coldness within Viola, as she struggled to empathize with others. This was until she met the as equally mysterious Z.W.E.L, who would become her travel companion. Eventually both would meet and be assisted by the legendary knight and warrior Siegfried, leader of the Schwarzwind who would shelter them from angry mobs. Siegfried would also ask them to assist Patroklos, he himself looking for his lost sister Pyrrha.

Creation

Viola is fictional character created for the Soul Calibur franchise, created by publisher Bandai Namco. The very mysterious fighter first appeared in Soul Calibur V released in 2012 and her design is attributed to Tomoko Imura. On the characters creation and design "The approval process for the draft went very smoothly, but for some reason I had a hard time carrying it to final version. This character design passed through quite a few hands before the costume was finalized. I focused on giving Viola and enigmatic facial expression."

Character Evolution

Viola's character and design came about from the merging of a few different ideas according to Takuji Kawano, including "an oracle" and an "Eastern European gypsy" as well as being mysterious and enigmatic.

Powers and Abilities

Viola is a skilled fighter and has a few supernatural like abilities. Viola utilizes a magical crystal ball and a metal claw in combat, with the former orbiting around her. She refers to her Crystal Ball as Quattuar Orbis.

Viola also has the supernatural ability to read other individuals futures. Specifically she uses two methods of divination. Western Style Tarot Card reading and Eastern style Moon divination, which uses her magical crystal ball. Some individuals she reads through her magical ball, give off a reddish tinge, reflected as a red moon. These individuals generally are also Malfested, individuals tainted by the Soul Edge weapon.

Physical Characteristics

  • Height: 5'2"
  • Weight: 108 lbs
  • Eyes: Violet
  • Hair: White

Other Media

Videogames

Soul Calibur V (2012)

Viola first appeared in the 2012 video game fighting franchise Soul Calibur V. Developed by Namco Bandai, for the Playstation 3 and X-Box 360. Her Japanese voice actress is Hitomi Nabatame and her English voice actress is Heather Hogan.
name: Viola

deck: A young Japanese-Chinese female, a master in the ancient art of Flamendo and the lead Character of Freaks Squeele.
description:
A young Japanese-Chinese female who has no superpowers whatsoever, but is a master in the ancient art of flamendo (a martial arts that combines flamenco dance moves with aikido styled combat). She has a peculiar hobby : forging weapons. She is the daughter of the head of the jakuza, and a candidate (by heritage) to succeed him. Her half-sister Wang Mu hates her and is bend on taking her place at the head of the family. Li Xiong herself is not interested that in the position, but also distrusts her sister. She takes up the position as head of the crime family, provided she can stay in France to terminate her acadamic study.

Her name in Chinese means Little Panda, but she is annoyed when people call her by that. She has feelings for Wong Fei Long, but finally falls for Ombre. Because she and Ombre spend some time in the underworld where the time moved faster, she has aged some years adn become smore mature then her friends.

His accomplices start distrusting him, assuming that his friendship with the girls will undermine his mission. He is very sensitive, likes stuffed animals and cares a lot for the smaller creatures of this world. His name can be translated as Wolfshade. By spending to years in the underworld with Li Xiong there love becomes a reality.

Brief History

Dust was scientist whom, together with his wife, tried to bring in powers to regular humans by drugs and light treatment. When his experiments led to the deaths of test-subjects, he and his wife fled from the law and started working more feverishly in giving humans meta-human abilities. To coerce Dazzler, the villain Dust possessed the body of her father, Carter Blaire. However, Dust's abilities caused the slow breakdown in the organic matter of the host, ultimately killing Carter. Alison and O.Z. fought Dust in Carter's body, leaving him for dead, and searching for Barbara London, who was being held by his counterpart, Silence.
